<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Proffer2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Proffer,</orth> vb. 1) to offer, to propose for acceptance: <bibl n="shak. jn 2.258" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 258</bibl> <cit><quote>(our --ed offer).</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.32" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 2, 32</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.252" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 252</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.3.71" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 71</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.2.9" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 2, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.1.19" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.196" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 196</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.196" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 196</bibl> <bibl n="shak. cym 3.5.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 5, 49</bibl>.<lb />2) to offer, to attempt to do sth.: <cit><quote>when time shall serve, be thou not slack to p., though she put thee back,</quote> <bibl n="shak. pp 334" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 334</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>